data.enText: a spirit who is believed to be a servant of God, and is sent by God to deliver a message or perform a task. Angels are often shown dressed in white, with wings.

data.chText: 安琪儿（指善良的人或可爱的小孩）；善人
data.enText: a person who is very good and kind; a child who behaves well

data.chText: 相信我，约翰绝非善良之辈。
data.enText: John is no angel , believe me (= he does not behave well) .

data.chText: 大好人（感激某人时所说）
data.enText: used when you are talking to sb and you are grateful to them

data.chText: 谢谢爸爸，你是个大好人。

data.enText: Be an angel and make me a cup of coffee.

means: 安琪儿(指善良的人或可爱的小孩)
大好人(感激某人时所说)

value.def: Angels are spiritual beings that some people believe are God's servants in heaven.
You can call someone you like very much an angel in order to show affection, especially when they have been kind to you or done you a favour.

example.ex: Thank you a thousand times, you're an angel.
example.tran: 万分感谢，你真是个大好人。

value.tran: （尤用于得到友好对待或帮助时）大好人，大善人

value.def: If you describe someone as an angel, you mean that they seem to be very kind and good.

example.ex: He was such an angel to put up with it.
example.tran: 他这都能忍，真是个大好人。

value.def: If you say that someone is on the side of the angels, you believe very strongly that what they are doing is right.

example.ex: Billy is on the side of the angels when it comes to racial tolerance.
example.tran: 说起种族间的包容，比利可真是宅心仁厚。

value.def: If you say that someone rushes in where angels fear to tread, you are criticizing them gently because they get themselves into dangerous or difficult situations without thinking carefully enough about what they are doing.

example.ex: Martin is inclined to rush in where angels fear to tread.
example.tran: 马丁总是喜欢贸然行事。

value.tran: 愚蠢地冒险;鲁莽行事;暴虎冯河
